Class SettingsPanel

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.awt.Component
      • java.awt.Container
        • javax.swing.JComponent
          • javax.swing.JPanel
            • menus.SettingsPanel
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.awt.image.ImageObserver, java.awt.MenuContainer, java.io.Serializable, javax.accessibility.Accessible

    public class SettingsPanel
extends javax.swing.JPanel
    The "SettingsPanel" class which extends JPanel. It allows the user to navigate and 'play with' specific game settings.
    Version:
    1.0, May 25 2014. (Created class to instantiate and access Sound class.), 1.1, May 26 2014. (Split toggle method into two to fix glitches - song would not start/stop properly and overlapped.), 1.2, May 30 2014. (Created a method to initialize clip in a separate method, added musicInitialized and getPanel method.), 1.3, June 8 2014. (Added menu button.), 1.4, June 10, 2014. (getMusicInitialized method and javadoc)
    Author:
    Chusa Nguyen
    See Also:
    Serialized Form
